### Smart Grid IoT - API Test Endpoints
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

### ==== HOMES ENDPOINTS ====

### Get all homes
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/homes

### Create a new home
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/homes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "homeId": "H011",
  "address": "999 Test Street",
  "owner": "Test User"
}

### ==== CONSUMPTION ENDPOINTS ====

### Get latest consumption for home H001
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/consumption/H001

### Get 24-hour consumption history for home H001
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/consumption/H001/history

### Get consumption history for home H002
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/consumption/H002/history

### Get consumption history for home H003
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/consumption/H003/history

### Get consumption history for home H004
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/consumption/H004/history

### Get consumption history for home H005
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/consumption/H005/history

### ==== ALERTS ENDPOINTS ====

### Get all recent alerts
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/alerts

### ==== STATISTICS ENDPOINTS ====

### Get overall statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/statistics

### ==== SYSTEM CHECK ====

### Check backend health (all homes)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/homes

### Check backend response time
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/statistics

### ==== NOTES ====
# To use these requests:
# 1. Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code (by Huachao Mao)
# 2. Click "Send Request" above any endpoint
# 3. View response in the side panel

# Available homes: H001 through H010
# High alert threshold: > 1200W
# Low alert threshold: < 250W
